Customer Churn Prediction¶

Churn is defined as the movement of customer from one company/bank to another. Churn rate usually lies in the range from 10% to 30%. The prediction model uses historical data on former churners and tries to find some similarity with existing customers. If some similarity is found those customers are classified as potential churners. A churner is a customer who closes his/her account or has decreased the number of transactions over a specific period of time.

Out[1]:

In this project, we will predict whether a customer will leave the bank or not based on the following factors:-

  1. Credit score
  2. Location of the Customer
  3. Gender
  4. Age
  5. Tenure
  6. Account Balance
  7. Number of Bank Products Customer Uses
  8. Has Credit Card
  9. Is Active Member
  10. Estimated Salary
